metadata.name: Orbs #5
metadata.description:
Serene orbs,
Playfully dynamic,
Soft visceral airy bodies,
Bold, colorful, at once moving, still, tiny, colossal,
Intimate organized chaos, both calm and ethereally energetic

(Created with p5.js and a WEBGL shader.)

metadata.name: Play with lines #zentangle #50
metadata.description:
Once upon a time, there was a sect called the Dotted and the Lined
They considered the point and line sacred!
And they believed that the world started with a point and moved with a line
And the points made the world!


Play with lines
This collection is the result of my playing with the lines I drew with the tablet.
And combining these lines with digital paintings in the background
This set has 7 layers
The first layer contains the background
The second layer of perlin noise lines
The third layer of the lines I have drawn with the tablet is 28 different images in the zentangle style
The fourth layer of lines
The fifth layer of forms on the collection
The sixth and seventh layers include the cover, frame, signature, etc.

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #51
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

metadata.name: Pedogenesis #14
metadata.description:
The shining waters with pale currents strewn,
The quiet fishing-smacks, the Eastern cove,
The semi-circle of its dark, green grove.
The luminous grasses, and the merry sun
In the grave sky; the sparkle far and wide,
Laughter of unseen children, cheerful chirp
Of crickets, and low lisp of rippling tide,
Light summer clouds fantastical as sleep
Changing unnoted while I gazed thereon.
All these fair sounds and sights I made my own.

2200 x 2200 pixel
Kiera Alodia, 2023

metadata.name: Obliques #74
metadata.description:
Obliques are a reinterpretation of Parallels, a collection of AI generated color fields by Marc Maurer. Many of the pieces in that collection are CC0, which basically means they can be reused for other projects, like this one.

Obliques takes artifacts from Parallels and uses them as brushes, painting slices of the original image on the canvas in a (hopefully) pleasant, chaotic way.

About 10% will be "Glitched".

The "Source Material" property will tell you the name of piece that it is using.

You can see Marc Maurer's Parallels project here:
https://objkt.com/collection/KT1TiSEcASGD19SW8bmqrqgSgCBkwXqDdTJ1

Obliques are also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

G : Toggle Grain
M : Toggle Matte
S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

metadata.name: Crab #8
metadata.description:
Immerse yourself in the nostalgic world of pixel art with "Crab" where the captivating form of a crab is meticulously crafted using the vibrant and colorful medium of pixels. Each square and line come together to form a playful representation of the crab, capturing its distinct shape and character uniquely and abstractly.

Made by p5.js
